snippet.title: Hind Ki Chadar | An Ode of Reverence & Sacrifice of Sri Guru Teg Bahadur Ji By Satinder Sartaaj
snippet.description:
#hindkichadar #gurutegbhadurji #satindersartaaj 

On The Sacred Occasion of THE 350th MARTYRDOM DAY of SRI GURU TEG BAHADUR JI, We're Presenting our Tribute "Hind Ki Chadar" | เจนเจฟเฉฐเจฆ เจเฉ เจเจพเจฆเจฐ | เคนเคฟเคเคฆ เคเฅ เคเคพเคฆเคฐ By Satinder Sartaaj. 

The legacy of Guru Tegh Bahadur Ji, the Ninth Guru of the Sikhs, radiates as an unfading constellation of courage, sacrifice, and eternal truth. Revered as โHind Ki Chadarโ โ the Sacred Shield of India, His supreme martyrdom did not belong to one faith alone, but became a benediction for all humanity โ safeguarding freedom of conscience, the sanctity of belief, and the dignity of the human spirit.

In this devotional offering, Dr. Satinder Sartaaj gathers the fragrance of centuries into verse, tracing the divine journey of the Guru โ from His serene birth in Guru-ke-Mahal to the transcendent moment in Delhi, where His luminous spirit embraced martyrdom and transformed Chandni Chowk into a sanctified ground of remembrance.
